<plot>Videotaped in the East Room of the White House, this concert, hosted by President and Mrs. Bush, presented a variety of music selections, including "O Mio Babbino Caro" from Puccini's "Gianni Schicchi", "I'm a Stranger Here Myself" from Kurt Weill's musical "Lost in the Stars", the jazz tune "I've Got the World on a String", and others. It also included readings from "American Mosaic: The Immigrant Experience in the Words of Those Who Lived It."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?262005</url></doc>
